header.gameNote: BASKETBALL TRAVELERS TIP-OFF TOURNEY AT EUGENE OR

article.headline: Oregon 95, UC Davis 64
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. (AP)Tajuan Porter scored 26 points and set the school record for career 3-pointers in Oregon's 95-64 victory against UC Davis Saturday afternoon in the BTI Tip-Off Tournament. The senior guard was 10 of 15 from the field and five of 10 on 3-point attempts. Porter came into the game needing three 3-pointers to break the school record of 282 set in 1995 by Orlando Williams. He tied the record and then broke it on back-to-back possessions midway through the first half to spark a 19-5 run that put the Ducks up 35-17 five minutes before halftime. LeKendric Longmire added 16 points for Oregon (2-0), which scored more than 90 points for the second this season after reaching that mark just once all of last season. Michael Dunigan also scored 11 and Teondre Williams had 10 points. Dominic Calegari scored 13 to pace the Aggies (0-2).
